    "narrative": "The Austin Waves enter today\u2019s slate with **Kyle Tucker** leading the charge, boasting an elite 76.90 efficiency score. His matchup against Alcantara is a primary target; the combination of a favorable wind direction and his consistent xwOBA metrics makes him our most bankable asset. **Jackson Merrill** also provides significant upside at 74.69, bolstered by his lead-off spot and a favorable platoon advantage against Taillon. Furthermore, **Josh Lowe** is a sneaky play at 72.21; while his raw base is modest, his elite speed profile\u2014weighted heavily given our focus on stealing bases\u2014combined with a slow-to-the-plate opposing pitcher makes him a critical component for our category goals today.\n\nThe most difficult decision on the bench involved **Miguel Vargas**, who landed at 58.56. While his projected efficiency is respectable, he ultimately fell short of **Nasim Nunez** and **Marcell Ozuna**, as the optimizer favored the more advantageous platoon and park factors inherent in their matchups. We are closely monitoring the status of **Gunnar Henderson** and **Jordan Westburg**; unfortunately, a rainout for the former and an IL stint for the latter have removed two high-ceiling contributors from our daily calculus. **Drake Baldwin** remains a marginal start at 47.27, as his matchup against Skubal presents a clear hurdle, requiring us to manage his expectations despite the need for depth at the catcher position.",
